  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "We're using the `ora` dependency to show a nice spinner. Examples [here](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/search?q=ora&unscoped_q=ora). \r\n\r\n`ora` goes straight to the console and skips any configured logger (e.g., `Config.logger`). In fact, it doesn't look like the logger configuration is even available in many places `ora` is used. This breaks the logger abstraction and prevents sending all output through a consumable interface. \r\n\r\n`ora` has a [stream](https://github.com/sindresorhus/ora#stream) feature, which may let us send its data through the same pipe. But this requires extending the logger abstraction to support streams (not a bad idea) or abstracting a stream sent to `ora` so it fits the logger abstraction (e.g., just log lines). \r\n\r\nUltimately, I wouldn't be surprised if we ditch the logger abstraction entirely, requiring the TTY to take care of it, but that would make Truffle harder to run in more abstract places (like the browser). \r\n\r\nHappy to dive into more detail if needed. Cheers! \r\n\r\n",
